OpenShift (oc) Command Cheatsheet 🔴
OpenShift uses the oc CLI — similar to kubectl but with extra features.

🔑 Login & Project
bashoc login https://api.cluster:6443 -u user -p pass  # Login to cluster
oc login --token=<token>                           # Login with token
oc whoami                                           # Show current user
oc whoami --show-server                             # Show cluster URL
oc projects                                         # List all projects
oc project myproject                                # Switch to a project
oc new-project myapp                                # Create new project

📦 Pods & Workloads
bashoc get pods                          # List pods in current project
oc get pods -o wide                  # Pods with node & IP info
oc get pods --all-namespaces         # Pods across all projects
oc describe pod <pod>                # Detailed pod info & events
oc logs <pod>                        # View pod logs
oc logs -f <pod>                     # Live stream logs
oc logs <pod> -c <container>         # Logs of specific container
oc rsh <pod>                         # Remote shell into pod
oc exec <pod> -- ls /app             # Run command inside pod
oc delete pod <pod>                  # Delete a pod

🚀 Deployments & Apps
bashoc new-app nginx                          # Deploy app from image
oc new-app https://github.com/user/repo   # Deploy from source (S2I)
oc get deployment                         # List deployments
oc get dc                                 # List deploymentconfigs (OpenShift specific)
oc rollout latest dc/<name>               # Trigger new deployment
oc rollout status dc/<name>               # Check rollout status
oc rollout undo dc/<name>                 # Rollback deployment
oc scale dc/<name> --replicas=3           # Scale up/down

🌐 Services, Routes & Networking
bashoc get svc                           # List services
oc expose svc/<name>                 # Create a route (expose externally)
oc get routes                        # List routes (OpenShift's ingress)
oc describe route <name>             # Route details & URL
oc get endpoints                     # Show service endpoints

Route = OpenShift's way to expose apps externally (like Ingress in K8s)


🔧 Build & Image (OpenShift Specific)
bashoc get builds                        # List builds
oc start-build <buildconfig>         # Start a new build
oc logs -f bc/<name>                 # Follow build logs
oc get bc                            # List build configs
oc get is                            # List image streams
oc import-image <name> --from=<img>  # Import external image

🔐 Users, Roles & Security (RBAC)
bashoc get users                                          # List users
oc get sa                                             # List service accounts
oc create sa myapp-sa                                 # Create service account
oc adm policy add-role-to-user edit user1 -n proj     # Give edit role
oc adm policy add-role-to-user admin user2            # Give admin role
oc adm policy add-scc-to-user anyuid -z myapp-sa      # Add Security Context Constraint
oc get scc                                            # List Security Context Constraints
oc policy add-role-to-user view user3                 # Read-only access

SCC (Security Context Constraints) = OpenShift's extra security layer controlling what pods can do


⚙️ Config & Secrets
bashoc get configmap                              # List configmaps
oc create configmap myconfig --from-file=app.properties
oc get secret                                 # List secrets
oc create secret generic mysecret --from-literal=password=1234
oc set env dc/<name> KEY=value                # Set environment variable
oc set volume dc/<name> --add --type=pvc      # Attach storage

📊 Resources & Quotas
bashoc get quota                         # List resource quotas
oc describe quota <name>             # Quota usage details
oc get limitrange                    # List limit ranges
oc adm top pods                      # Pod CPU/memory usage
oc adm top nodes                     # Node resource usage

🩺 Troubleshooting (Most Used in Support)
bashoc get events --sort-by='.lastTimestamp'   # Recent events (find issues)
oc describe pod <pod>                       # Check Events section for errors
oc logs <pod> --previous                    # Logs of crashed/restarted pod
oc get pods -o wide                         # Which node pod is running on
oc debug node/<node-name>                   # Debug a node
oc status                                   # Overview of current project
oc adm node-logs <node>                     # Node level logs

🔍 oc vs kubectl — Key Differences
Feature           kubectl                         oc (OpenShift)
Projects          namespaces                      projects (namespace + extras)
Expose app        Ingress                         Routes
Deployment        Deployment                      DeploymentConfig + Deployment
Build             ❌                              BuildConfig + S2I
Security          PSP                             SCCImage 
registry          external                        built-in ImageStream
